      "name": "CVE-2025-55182",
      "description": "An unauthenticated remote code execution (RCE) vulnerability in React Server Components, also known as React2Shell. Allows attackers to execute arbitrary code with the privileges of the user running the affected web server process. Affects react-server-dom-webpack, react-server-dom-parcel, and react-server-dom-turbopack versions 19.0, 19.1.0, 19.1.1, and 19.2.0. CVSS v3.x score: 10.0, CVSS v4 score: 9.3.",
      "external_references": [
        {
          "source_name": "CVE",
          "external_id": "CVE-2025-55182",
